<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="709" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[747,1338,307,734]" lastBlockId="18.[130,1340,740,1721]" pageId="18" pageNumber="709">
<emphasis box="[747,1025,307,340]" pageId="18" pageNumber="709">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body c¢.5457 mm, tail 51-58 mm, ear 10-12 mm, hindfoot 6-8 mm, forearm 42-45 mm; weight 7-9-1 g. Dorsal pelage of the Sororcula Long-fingered Bat is notably dense, relatively long, slightly silky, and rich dark brown; ventral pelage has similar texture but is slightly paler. Dorsal pelage occasionally approaches medium dark brown. Wing membrane and uropatagium are dark brownish black and have no noticeable change in color across their surfaces. Dorsally, particularly close to humerus head, and ventrally, there is a slight extension of body pelage onto wing membranes. Tragus (6-8 mm) is relatively long, with curved projection and laterally thickened base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="709" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="18.[130,1340,740,1721]" pageId="18" pageNumber="709">
<emphasis box="[132,244,858,891]" pageId="18" pageNumber="709">Habitat.</emphasis>
Remnant native vegetation, open savanna areas, and probably transformed and degraded habitats at elevations of 40-2200 m (mostly above 900 m). Natural forests near roosts of Sororcula Long-fingered Bats have mostly been cleared and replaced with introduced trees.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="709" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph blockId="18.[130,1340,740,1721]" pageId="18" pageNumber="709">
<emphasis box="[132,395,1017,1050]" pageId="18" pageNumber="709">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
There is no specific information recorded for this species, but it is expected to mainly eat soft insects captured in flight as do other long-fingered bats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[132,506,1095,1128]" pageId="18" pageNumber="709" type="breeding">
<paragraph blockId="18.[130,1340,740,1721]" box="[132,506,1095,1128]" pageId="18" pageNumber="709">
<emphasis box="[132,267,1095,1128]" pageId="18" pageNumber="709">Breeding.</emphasis>
